In England, in the seven days to 05 February, there were 473,483 new confirmed cases (837.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 January, there were 604,538 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 22% (131,055 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 10 February is 15,501,331 (27,411.7 cases per 100,000 population).
